text: Elizabeth of England and Scotland (1635–1650) was the second daughter of King Charles I of England and Scotland and Henrietta Maria of France. Elizabeth was born on 28 December 1635 at St. James's Palace, and was baptized there on 2 January the next year by William Laud, the Archbishop of Canterbury.She died on the Isle of Wright in 1650 at the age of 14 during commonwealth.
